 the spectral index and an\nincrease of the linear polarization to a large fraction (~50%) of the total\nflux, as well as a rotation of the electric vector position angle. These are\nconsistent with a transformation from a self-absorbed compact jet to\noptically-thin ejecta -- the first time such a discrete ejection has been\nobserved in a failed outburst -- and may imply a complex magnetic field\ngeometry.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Sep 2013 10:54:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 19 Nov 2013 10:43:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
